The paper focuses on visual query systems (VQSs) and their role in data exploration workflows, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and information retrieval (IR) aspects. The paper also discusses the design and evaluation of VQSs, which can fall under the categories of database (DB) and visualization (VIS). Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which can be related to computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.HCI, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.VIS, and cs.CL.
